              Can use sliding window?
                   |
        +----------+-----------+
        |                      |
   Only positive nums?     Negative nums?
        |                      |
     Yes ✅                No ❌
        |                      |
Sum/length/frequency?    Use Prefix Sum + Map or Brute Force
        |
     Yes ✅
        |
Use Sliding Window
| Data Structure | When Used                             |
| -------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| HashSet        | For uniqueness (e.g., substrings)     |
| HashMap        | For character counts/frequency        |
| Deque          | For sliding max/min (monotonic queue) |
| Prefix Sum     | For negatives or complex conditions   |
| Arrays         | For simple counting (fixed charset)   |

| Problem                     | Pattern           | Example      |
| --------------------------- | ----------------- | ------------ |
| Maximum sum of k elements   | Fixed-size window | Leetcode 643 |
| Average of subarrays size k | Fixed-size window | Leetcode 643 |

| Problem                                       | Pattern                   | Notes                       |
| --------------------------------------------- | ------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| Leetcode 3 – Longest Substring Without Repeat | Dynamic, grow/shrink      | Use HashSet                 |
| Leetcode 76 – Minimum Window Substring        | Dynamic + Frequency count | Use HashMap                 |
| Leetcode 209 – Min Subarray Sum ≥ Target      | Dynamic, sum ≥ target     | Only with **positive** nums |

| Problem                              | Why                   | Solution                    |
| ------------------------------------ | --------------------- | --------------------------- |
| Leetcode 560 – Subarray Sum Equals K | Negative allowed      | Prefix sum + HashMap        |
| Leetcode 53 – Maximum Subarray       | Can't shrink reliably | Kadane’s Algorithm (Greedy) |

# When Sliding window fails
| Scenario                                         | Why It Fails                            | Use Instead                               |
| ------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| Array contains **negative numbers**              | Window sum becomes unreliable           | Prefix sum + binary search or brute force |
| Need **exact sum** with positive & negative      | Can’t shrink window properly            | Prefix sum + HashMap (e.g., Leetcode 560) |
| Need **global maximum/minimum** (not contiguous) | Window can’t find non-contiguous values | Greedy or Divide & Conquer                |
| Searching for **unordered subsequence**          | Not contiguous                          | Hashing or 2 pointers                     |
